Date: 7 Apr 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Associated Press [edited
On Friday, French officials said that a case of BSE had been discovered in
an animal born in 1997 -- after special measures on animal feed had been
put into effect in July 1996. The cow, born in August 1997, was destroyed
along with its herd.
Specialists must now determine why the cow, found in the Seine-Maritime
region, was infected with BSE. Feed containing animal parts can carry the
disease, but such feed is forbidden in France.
[Byline: Chris Fontaine, AP London
